 confidence from john wilkes this afternoon ashley is 
 going to marry miss melanie be announced tomorrow 
 night at the ball 
 scarlett i believe it 
 mr here here what are you after scarlett 
 what are you about have you been making a spectacle 
 of yourself running about after a man not in love 
 with you when you might have any of the bucks in the 
 county 
 scarlett i been running after him 
 just a surprise all 
 mr now be jerking your chin at me if 
 ashley wanted to marry you it would be with misgivings 
 say yes i want my girl to be happy not be happy 
 with him 
 scarlett i would i would 
 mr what difference does it make whom you 
 marry so long as a southerner and thinks like you 
 and when gone i leave tara to you 
 scarlett i want tara plantations mean 
 anything when 
 mr do you mean to toll me katie scarlett 
 that tara that land mean anything to you why 
 
 land is the only thing in the world worth working for 
 worth fighting for worth dying for because the only 
 thing that lasts 
 scarlett oh paw you talk like an irishman 
 mr proud i am that irish and you 
 be forgetting missy that too and to 
 anyone with a drop of irish blood in them why the land 
 they live on is like their mother oh but there there now 
 just a child come to you this love of the land 
 no getting away from it if irish 
 next day the drive to twelve oaks for the 
 barbeque there 
 mr well john wilkes a grand day 
 be having for the barbecue 
 john wilkes so it seems gerald why mrs 
 hara with you 
