 too something hope be glad to hear now come 
 and say hello to my cousin melanie wilkes 
 scarlett oh do we have to 
 ashley been looking forward to seeing you again 
 melanie scarlett 
 melanie scarlett so glad to see you again 
 scarlett melanie hamilton what a surprise to run 
 into you here i hope going to stay with us a few 
 days at least 
 melanie i hope i shall stay long enough for us to become 
 real friends scarlett i do so want us to be 
 ashley keep her here we scarlett 
 scarlett oh just have to make the biggest fuss 
 over her we ashley and if anybody who 
 knows how to give a girl a good time ashley though 
 i expect our good times must seem terribly silly to you 
 because so serious 
 melanie oh scarlett you have so much life always 
 admired you so i wish i could be more like you 
 scarlett you flatter me melanie and say 
 things you mean 
 ashley nobody could accuse melanie of being insincere 
 could they my dear 
 scarlett oh well then not like you is she 
 ashley ashley never means a word he says to any girl 
 oh why charles hamilton you handsome old thing you 
 charles hamilton but oh miss 
 scarlett do you think that was kind to bring your 
 brother down here just to break my poor 
 simple heart 
 india and sue ellen are watching scarlett in distance 
 ellen look at scarlett never even noticed charles 
 before now just because your beau after him 
 like a hornet 
 scarlett charles hamilton i want to eat barbecue 
 with you and mind you go philandering with any 
 other girl because mighty jealous 
 
 charles hamilton i miss i 
 scarlett i do declare frank kelly you look dashing with 
 that new set of whiskers frank oh thank you thank you miss 
 scarlett scarlett you know charles hamilton and ray kelvert 
 asked me to eat barbecue with them but i told them i 
 because promised you be so amused look at 
 her after your beau now 
 frank oh mighty flattering of you miss scarlett see what 
 i can do miss scarlett kathleen your sister so mad 
 about scarlett you sparking her beau 
 scarlett as if i get a better beau than that old maid in 
 britches brent and stew do talk you handsome old thing 
 no not i mean to say that mad at you brent why 
 scarlett honey 
 scarlett you been near me all day and i wore this old 
 dress just because i thought you liked it i was counting on eating 
 barbecue with you two brent well you are scarlett stew of 
 course you are honey scarlett oh i never can make up my 
 mind which of you handsomer i was awake all last night trying 
 to figure it out kathleen that kathleen who 
 scarlett that man looking at us and smiling a nasty dog 
 kathleen my dear you know rhett 
 butler from charleston he has the most terrible 
 reputation 
 scarlett he looks as if as if he knows what i looked 
 like without my shimmy 
 kathleen how but my dear he received 
 had to spend most of his time up north because his folks 
 in charleston even speak to him he was expelled 
 from west point so fast and then that 
 business about that girl he marry 
 tell 
 kathleen well he took her out in a buggy riding in 
 the late afternoon without a chaperone and then and then 
 he refused to marry her 
 scarlett whisper 
 kathleen no but she was ruined just the same 
 ashley and melanie on the balcony open to the garden 
 melanie ashley 
 ashley happy 
 melanie so happy 
 ashley you seem to belong here as if it had all been 
 imagined for you 
 melanie i like to feel that i belong to the things you 
 love 
 ashley you love twelve oaks as i do 
 melanie yes ashley i love it as as more than a house 
 a whole world that wants only to be graceful and 
 beautiful 
 ashley and so unaware that it may not last forever melanie 
 afraid of what may happen when the war conies you 
 well we have to be afraid for us no war can come into our 
 world ashley whatever comes love you just as i do now until i die 
 
 
 
 
 
